Pursuant to the provisions of Articles 76 and 77 of the Organic Law for the Protection of Personal Data, the Authority for the Protection of Personal Data will be the Superintendence of Data Protection, which once constituted will act as the control and surveillance body in charge of guaranteeing all citizens the protection of their personal data, and of carrying out all necessary actions to ensure that the principles, rights, guarantees and procedures provided for in the Law and its implementing regulations are respected.Last modified 15 Dec 2021
				
			